==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia|Phonological history of English short A}}
'''[[bad]]-[[lad]] [[split]]'''

#{{linguistics}} a [[phonemic split]] of the phoneme /æ/ into a short /æ/ and a long /æː/, as heard in some varieties of British and Australian English, in which "bad" is pronounced /bæːd/ and "lad" is pronounced /læd/

